HEADWORD: Phonetics
<hw>Pho*net"ics</hw> <pr>(f⟦osl⟧*n⟦ecr⟧t"⟦icr⟧ks)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<sn>1.</sn> <def>The doctrine or science of sounds; especially those of
the human voice; phonology.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>The art of representing vocal sounds by signs and
written characters.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Phonetism</ent>⟦br⟧
